  "_meta": {
    "format_version": 1,
    "authored_from": "§5.1 (fixed-template canonical serializer) + §5.2 (claim shape) + §5.3 (kind enum) + RFC 8785 (minimal string escaping rules), cross-service-contract 2026-05-25",
    "author": "ChrisPachulski",
    "date": "2026-05-25",
    "reviewed_by": "ChrisPachulski",
    "test_key_hex": "544553545f5345435245545f33325f43484152535f46495845445f56414c55455f58",
    "notes": [
      "Byte template (§5.1): {\"exp\":<int>,\"iat\":<int>,\"jti\":\"<26-char ULID>\",\"k\":\"<kind>\",\"nbf\":<int>,\"rid\":\"<resourceId>\",\"sub\":\"<sub>\",\"v\":1}",
      "Key order is alphabetical: exp, iat, jti, k, nbf, rid, sub, v. No whitespace. UTF-8 output.",
      "Integers: bare decimal, no leading zeros, no decimal point, no exponent.",
      "Strings: minimal JSON escaping only (double-quote, backslash, \\n \\r \\t \\b \\f, \\uXXXX for U+0000–U+001F). No other escaping.",
      "HMAC: HMAC-SHA256 over canonical UTF-8 bytes using the fixed test secret.",
      "expectedHmacSecret length: 34 bytes (TEST_SECRET_32_CHARS_FIXED_VALUE_X).",
      "jti values are 26-char Crockford Base32 ULIDs (charset: 0-9 A-H J K M N P-T V-Z — no I, L, O, U).",
      "These vectors are the ground truth for TS (D1), Rust (M2+), and Swift (M2+). No implementation is the authority — the spec is.",
      "Catchup rid format per §5.2: streamId|startUtc|durationMin (pipe is not a JSON special char; no escaping needed).",
      "playlist-90d uses a valid SIWA apple sub per §8.3 pattern: [0-9]{6}\\.[0-9a-f]{32}\\.[0-9]{4}.",
      "series-basic uses a local sub per §8.3 pattern: local:[0-9A-HJKMNP-TV-Z]{26} (uppercase Crockford Base32 ULID).",
      "vod-basic sub is plex:0 — tests the edge case where plex id is exactly zero (valid per §8.3: plex:(0|[1-9][0-9]*))."
    ]
  },
